{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014RxX5TPvJTETfKntNcyJsh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pipeline has completed successfully. Here's a summary of the full diagnosis and fix:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis & Fix Summary\n\n### Root Cause: Data Skew in Stage 3\n\nThe diagnostic evidence confirmed:\n- **100,000 total records** across 1,000 distinct user_ids\n- **user_id 999 holds 50,000 records** (~50% of the entire dataset)\n- **Skew ratio: 500x** (far above the 10x threshold)\n\nWhen Stage 3 ran `GROUP BY user_id`, all 50,000 records for user_id 999 were shuffled into a single executor. With only 256MB executor memory, that partition caused an `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n### Fix Applied (Options B + C combined)\n\nThe `etl-job.yaml` was patched with two changes:\n\n```yaml\n--conf spark.executor.memory=1g                    # raised from 256m (4x increase)\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true             # enable AQE\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true    # split hot partitions automatically\n```\n\n- **Increased executor memory** (`256m → 1g`) gives each executor enough headroom to handle the hot partition.\n- **AQE skewJoin** detects skewed partitions at runtime and splits them into smaller sub-partitions, spreading the user_id 999 work across multiple tasks rather than one.\n\n### Verification\n\n```\nJob status: Complete (1/1)\nFinal log line: spark_etl_pipeline_verified\n```\n\nThe job ran all three stages and exited with code 0. All success criteria met."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":614,"cache_read_input_tokens":40956,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":614},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24f05627-cc47-4372-9962-e7aa3c496